<subSubSection id="A7CC2DBDFFC0FFEBFF6BFF3AFE4CFD23" pageId="26" pageNumber="301" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFC0FFEBFF6BFF3AFE62FE63" blockId="26.[151,1130,220,691]" pageId="26" pageNumber="301">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC0FFEBFF6BFF3AFEB6FF43" bold="true" box="[151,264,220,243]" pageId="26" pageNumber="301">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFC0FFEBFEF3FF3AFE1DFF43" author="BLAKE" box="[271,419,220,243]" firstAuthor="BLAKE" pageId="26" pageNumber="301" pagination="231 - 239" refId="ref47639" refString="BLAKE D. H. 1939: Eight new Chrysomelidae (Coleoptera) from the Dominican Republic. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington 41: 231 - 239." type="journal article" year="1939">BLAKE (1939)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC0FFEBFDE5FF3AFCACFF43" authorityName="Blake" authorityYear="1939" box="[537,786,220,243]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Paratrikona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubescens">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC0FFEBFDE5FF3AFCACFF43" box="[537,786,220,243]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="301">Paratrikona rubescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Jarabacoa and added that 
<collectingRegion id="2D12B0D4FFC0FFEBFF6BFF1AFEB3FEA3" box="[151,269,252,275]" country="United Kingdom" name="Darlington" pageId="26" pageNumber="301">Darlington</collectingRegion>
wrote that the specimens were ‘rather deep red with conspicuous white blotches irregularly arranged’ while only slight trace of the white markings remained on the dried specimens; as a result, Blake did not indicate them in her drawings. 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFC0FFEBFC2DFEDAFBD8FEE3" author="BLAKE" box="[977,1126,316,339]" firstAuthor="BLAKE" pageId="26" pageNumber="301" pagination="269 - 282" refId="ref47670" refString="BLAKE D. H. 1971: Fifteen new West Indian chrysomelid beetles. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington 73: 269 - 282." type="journal article" year="1971">BLAKE (1971)</bibRefCitation>
published additional specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC0FFEBFDE0FEBAFD18FEC3" authorityName="Blake" authorityYear="1939" box="[540,678,348,371]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Paratrikona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubescens">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC0FFEBFDE0FEBAFD18FEC3" box="[540,678,348,371]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="301">P. rubescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected at ‘Arroya de Toro, Quebrada Honda’ including a figure showing clear white markings. 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFC0FFEBFCD4FE9AFC4AFE23" author="BOROWIEC" box="[808,1012,380,403]" firstAuthor="BOROWIEC" pageId="26" pageNumber="301" pagination="567 - 570" refId="ref48480" refString="BOROWIEC L. 2009 b: Paratrikona albomaculata, a new species from the Dominican Republic (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Cassidinae: Dorynotini). Genus 20: 567 - 570." type="journal article" year="2009" yearSuffix="b">BOROWIEC (2009b)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC0FFEBFF6BFE7AFEF7FE03" authorityName="Borowiec" authorityYear="2009" box="[151,329,412,435]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Paratrikona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albomaculata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC0FFEBFF6BFE7AFEF7FE03" box="[151,329,412,435]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="301">P. albomaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Jarabacoa and separated it from other species based on the conspicuous white pattern on elytra.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFC0FFEBFF49FE3AFE4CFD23" blockId="26.[151,1130,220,691]" pageId="26" pageNumber="301">
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC0FFEBFF49FE3AFE6FFE43" authorityName="Borowiec" authorityYear="2009" box="[181,465,476,499]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Paratrikona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albomaculata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC0FFEBFF49FE3AFE6FFE43" box="[181,465,476,499]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="301">Paratrikona albomaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has clearly marked, contrasting white spots on reddish-brown elytra while the 
<typeStatus id="306DC094FFC0FFEBFEBFFE1AFE1EFDA3" box="[323,416,508,531]" pageId="26" pageNumber="301">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC0FFEBFE3FFE1AFDF6FDA3" authorityName="Blake" authorityYear="1939" box="[451,584,508,531]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Paratrikona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubescens">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC0FFEBFE3FFE1AFDF6FDA3" box="[451,584,508,531]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="301">P. rubescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the spots only slightly indicated. Nevertheless, they are on exactly same position as in 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC0FFEBFDCBFDFAFD5AFD83" authorityName="Borowiec" authorityYear="2009" box="[567,740,540,563]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Paratrikona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albomaculata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC0FFEBFDCBFDFAFD5AFD83" box="[567,740,540,563]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="301">P. albomaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both taxa also have identical punctation of elytra and pronotum, similar convexity of elytra, identical M-shaped black pattern of prontum, and are thus in my opinion conspecific. For these reasons I synonymized 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC0FFEBFBAFFDBAFE94FD23" authorityName="Borowiec" authorityYear="2009" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Paratrikona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albomaculata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC0FFEBFBAFFDBAFE94FD23" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="301">P. albomaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC0FFEBFE9BFD9AFE52FD23" authorityName="Blake" authorityYear="1939" box="[359,492,636,659]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Paratrikona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubescens">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC0FFEBFE9BFD9AFE52FD23" box="[359,492,636,659]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="301">P. rubescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
